---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Privacy Policy | burninjurycalc.com';
const description = 'How burninjurycalc.com handles your data, including analytics, advertising cookies, the case-review form, and your rights under GDPR, CCPA, and other privacy laws.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><em>Last updated: July 2026.</em></p>

  <p>burninjurycalc.com ("the Site") is operated by The Click Lab Agency LLC ("we," "us," "our"). This Privacy Policy describes what information we collect, how we use it, who we share it with, and what rights you have. We've written it in plain language because the burn-injury content on this site reaches people in difficult circumstances, and clarity about data handling matters.</p>

  <h2>Summary</h2>
  <p>Short version: browsing the calculator or reading any guide requires no account and collects nothing about you beyond ordinary analytics (Section 4). Submitting the case-review form on our homepage is different: it collects your name, phone number, email address, case details, and a timestamp of your consent, and that information is shared with one or more attorneys or their agents so they can evaluate your situation and contact you about it. Sections 1&ndash;3 below explain exactly what's collected and shared if you use that form, and how to opt out. We also use Google Analytics to understand traffic patterns and display ads served by Google AdSense, which uses cookies to show relevant ads. You can opt out of personalized advertising at any time via Google's ad settings.</p>

  <h2>1. Information you provide directly</h2>
  <p>The calculator on this Site is client-side. When you enter burn details, pre-injury income, age, and state to compute an estimated recovery range, those values are processed in your browser and are not transmitted to our servers. We do not log calculator inputs.</p>
  <p>If you submit the case-review form (labeled "Burn Injury" case review on our homepage), we collect your name, phone number, email address, a description of your case, and a timestamp recording that you agreed to the consent language shown next to the form. See Section 2 for exactly what happens to that information.</p>
  <p>If you choose to email us instead, the contents of your email (sender address, body, and any attachments) are received by our email provider and retained for as long as needed to handle the conversation. We don't sell or share the contents of that email.</p>

  <h2>2. What happens if you submit the case-review form</h2>
  <p>If you submit the case-review form, your name, phone number, email address, and case details are shared with one or more attorneys or their agents licensed to practice in your jurisdiction, so they can evaluate your situation and contact you about it. The Click Lab Agency LLC, which operates burninjurycalc.com, is not a law firm, does not provide legal advice, and does not vet, endorse, or guarantee the attorneys in this network. Submitting the form does not create an attorney-client relationship with The Click Lab Agency LLC or with any attorney until and unless that attorney separately agrees to represent you. The Click Lab Agency LLC may be compensated for these referrals.</p>
  <p>By submitting the form, you separately consent to be contacted by phone, text, and email — including by automated dialing technology — by The Click Lab Agency LLC and the attorneys or agents your information is shared with. That consent is not required to use any other part of this site, and you can decline it by not submitting the form.</p>

  <h2>3. Opting out</h2>
  <p>The simplest opt-out is not to submit the case-review form — browsing the calculator and every guide on this Site never requires it and never shares your information with anyone. If you've already submitted the form and want your information removed or want to stop being contacted, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <strong>[OPT-OUT]</strong>, or visit <a href="https://theclicklab.agency/optout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">theclicklab.agency/optout</a>. We'll process the request and pass it along to any attorney or agent your information was shared with.</p>

  <h2>4. Information collected automatically</h2>
  <p>Like virtually all modern websites, our hosting provider's edge layer and our analytics provider receive some automatically-transmitted data from every visit. This typically includes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your IP address (used to determine approximate location for analytics, discarded after standard retention).</li>
    <li>Browser type and version, operating system, device type, and screen resolution.</li>
    <li>Referrer URL (the page you came from, if any).</li>
    <li>The pages you visit on this Site and how long you spend on each.</li>
    <li>Generic events like page-loads and outbound link clicks.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
  <p>This Site uses a small number of cookies, split by purpose:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Strictly necessary cookies</strong> &mdash; storing privacy preferences themselves.</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics cookies</strong> &mdash; Google Analytics cookies that distinguish your session from other visitors'.</li>
    <li><strong>Advertising cookies</strong> &mdash; Google AdSense cookies for ad personalization. You can opt out via Google's ad settings (see Section 7).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Google Analytics</h2>
  <p>We use Google Analytics 4 in a default-privacy configuration: IP addresses are truncated before storage, ad personalization signals are disabled where possible, and we don't merge GA data with personally identifying user profiles. Google's data handling for Analytics is described at <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites</a>. To opt out of GA entirely, install Google's browser opt-out: <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout</a>.</p>

  <h2>7. Google AdSense advertising</h2>
  <p>This Site displays ads from Google AdSense (publisher ID pub-6434377544325972). When AdSense renders an ad, Google uses cookies to (a) prevent fraudulent ad clicks, (b) frequency-cap which ads you see, and (c) optionally personalize the ads. You can review and adjust Google's ad personalization settings at <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">adssettings.google.com</a> or opt out of third-party ad personalization via <a href="https://aboutads.info" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">aboutads.info</a> or (EU/UK) <a href="https://youronlinechoices.eu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">youronlinechoices.eu</a>.</p>
  <p>Opting out of personalized advertising does not stop ads from appearing; it stops them being matched to your inferred interests.</p>

  <h2>8. Other third parties</h2>
  <p>Beyond the attorneys or agents your information goes to if you submit the case-review form (Section 2), and beyond Google Analytics and Google AdSense, the only other third parties that may see data about your visit are our hosting provider's CDN and any third-party site you click through to (e.g., state agency pages, court opinions linked from guides). We don't sell or share data with data brokers, and browsing the Site without submitting the form never results in your information being sold or shared with anyone.</p>

  <h2>9. Your rights under GDPR (EEA, UK)</h2>
  <p>If you're in the EEA or UK, the GDPR gives you several rights: access, rectification, erasure, restriction, portability, and objection. To exercise these, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>. We'll respond within 30 days. Legal basis for our processing is generally (a) your consent — for non-essential cookies, and separately for the case-review form and the automated-contact consent described in Section 2, both of which you may withdraw at any time using the opt-out methods in Section 3 — and (b) our legitimate interest in operating, securing, and improving the Site.</p>

  <h2>10. Your rights under CCPA / CPRA (California)</h2>
  <p>California residents have the right to know what personal information we collect, to delete personal information, to opt out of "sale" or "sharing" of personal information, and to non-discrimination for exercising any of these rights. Two things can qualify as a "sale" or "sharing" under California law: the use of advertising cookies (see Section 7), and sharing your case-review submission with attorneys or their agents for compensation (see Section 2) — you can opt out of either using the controls in Section 7 or Section 3, respectively. Anonymous browsing of the calculator and guides is never sold or shared. To exercise other CCPA rights, contact <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>

  <h2>11. Do Not Track</h2>
  <p>We honor DNT signals to the extent that, when DNT is on, we disable advertising personalization. We don't disable analytics on DNT alone. For analytics-off entirely, use the GA opt-out plugin.</p>

  <h2>12. Children's privacy (COPPA)</h2>
  <p>This Site is intended for adults dealing with burn-injury matters. We don't knowingly collect information from children under 13, including through the case-review form. If you believe we have, contact us at <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> and we'll delete it.</p>

  <h2>13. Security</h2>
  <p>HTTPS on all pages, no user accounts, limited access to admin accounts, and case-review submissions are transmitted only to the attorneys or agents they're shared with. Standard practices for a static informational site with a single lead form.</p>

  <h2>14. International transfers</h2>
  <p>Our hosting provider and Google's services may process data outside your country (typically the United States). We rely on standard contractual clauses where required.</p>

  <h2>15. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>We update this policy as needed. When we do, we update the "Last updated" date at the top. Material changes will be announced on the home page. Continued use of the Site after a change indicates acceptance.</p>

  <h2>16. Contact</h2>
  <p>Privacy questions or opt-out requests: <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
